<P>But you believe what you then &s;p<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ke was true.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Clows.</SPEAKER>
<P>Without doubt, and I hope Mr <HI>Co&s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ns</HI> took <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> truly to write down what I then delivered; but whether he did expre&s;s my meaning right or no, I know not; for I did not look over his Notes till the Day I &s;aw them at your Chamber</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Solicitor.</SPEAKER>
<P>Was not the a&s;&s;embly called an Illegal A&s;&s;embly? and that they had made Acts prejudicial to the Country.</P>
